Finely chop @red onion{1/2} and lightly crush the @pistachio nuts{2}. Shred or
finely slice the @baby gem lettuce{1}. Chop the @cherry tomatoes{1} in half.
Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{4} and drain and rinse the @mixed beans{1}.

Heat @olive oil{1%tbsp} in a #frying pan{} on medium-low heat. Once hot, cook
your red onion gently for ~{5%minutes} then add the mixed beans and
@habanero sauce{2}. Next, add the @tomato purée{1}, @cumin{3/4} and
@water{5%tbsp}. Season with @salt{1/4%tsp} and a pinch of @pepper{pinch}. Cook
with a lid on for ~{15%minutes}.

Take a quick siesta.

Take out two-thirds of the beans and mash them up to a paste using the back of a
#fork{}. Now mix the remaining whole beans from the pan into the paste. Check
for seasoning and voila, they're done!

Heat a frying pan on medium high heat. Spread half of the refried beans across
@super soft tortillas with whole wheat{4}. Place the tortilla into the pan (bean
side up!) and scatter over some of the cheese, half of the pistachio nuts and a
squeeze of @lime juice{1/2}. Tip: To get more juice out of your lime roll it
firmly under your hand against the #chopping board{} first to loosen it up.

Place another tortilla across the top and after ~{3%minutes} carefully flip the
quesadilla over. Tip: We don't recommend the 'pancake flip' unless you are a
total pancake pro! Cook for another ~{3%minutes} on the other side before
removing to a warm #plate{}. Cook the other quesadilla in the same way.

Drizzle @olive oil{1%tsp} and a little squeeze of lime juice over the tomatoes
and lettuce. Gently toss together with the tips of your fingers and season with
@salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}.

Cut your quesadillas into quarters and put a good dollop of
@sour cream{3} on top. Grate over a bit of lime zest and drizzle on a little
more lime juice. Serve the salad on the side. Ándale!